{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the network upgrade project, provision an epipe service 'Epipe-VLAN-1715-remote-site-to-edge-site'. Customer 8827 requires a point-to-point connection. Source router: 192.168.170.36, port: lag-Cisco7-4x10GE. Destination router: 192.168.125.99, port: lag-Arista9-2x25GE. Common VLAN: 1715. Service ID: 9745. MTU: 1450. Use existing SDPs 3699 and 9936."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1715-remote-site-to-edge-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8827,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9745,\n    \"mtu\": 1450,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.170.36\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Cisco7-4x10GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1715,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.125.99\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Arista9-2x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1715,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"3699\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.170.36\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.125.99\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"9936\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.125.99\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.170.36\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need a new L3 VPN service for customer 4886. The service is called 'VPRN-1178-FlexNet' with one site at 192.168.133.53. NE service ID: 1178. RD: 64659:1178. VRF import: FlexNet-VRF-Import, export: FlexNet-VRF-Export. Please configure these interfaces: Pluto-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c11/4 with IP 10.14.215.21/28; Pluto-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Mellanox5-2x25GE with IP 172.30.160.28/31; Pluto-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Dell-NAR1-4x25GE with IP 100.84.65.83/31."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-1178-FlexNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4886,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-1178-FlexNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.133.53\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 1178,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64659:1178\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"FlexNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"FlexNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Pluto-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/2/c11/4\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.14.215.21\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Pluto-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.po