{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the PathFinder project, deploy a VPRN named 'VPRN-4399-PathFinder' for customer 7517. Two sites needed: Site 1 (192.168.50.51): service ID 4399, RD 65069:4399, VRF PathFinder-VRF-Import/PathFinder-VRF-Export, interfaces: Polaris-Cluster-Master on port lag-Cisco11-4x25GE with IP 100.100.23.43/31; Polaris-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/1/c8/4 with IP 10.154.152.202/28. Site 2 (192.168.111.1): service ID 4399, RD 64815:4399, VRF PathFinder-VRF-Import/PathFinder-VRF-Export, interfaces: Theta-Cluster-Master on port 2/1/c11/1 with IP 10.234.213.200/30; Theta-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Broadcom12-2x100GE with IP 10.151.116.29/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-4399-PathFinder\",\n    \"customer-id\": 7517,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-4399-PathFinder\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.50.51\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 4399,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65069:4399\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"PathFinder-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"PathFinder-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Polaris-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Cisco11-4x25GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.1