{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Can you create VPRN 'VPRN-8876-FlexNet' connecting two customer sites? Customer ID: 8257. Device 192.168.199.51 has service ID 8876, RD 64513:8876, VRF import/export: FlexNet-VRF-Import/FlexNet-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Delta-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c3/2 with IP 10.226.42.38/30; Delta-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-AFOR6-2x100GE with IP 172.25.250.56/31. Device 192.168.240.25 has service ID 8876, RD 65287:8876, VRF import/export: FlexNet-VRF-Import/FlexNet-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Pulsar-Cluster-Master on port 2/2/c7/4 with IP 10.243.55.97/31; Pulsar-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-AMD7-2x25GE with IP 100.101.20.156/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-8876-FlexNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8257,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-8876-FlexNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.199.51\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 8876,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64513:8876\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"FlexNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"FlexNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Delta-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/2/c3/2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.226.42.38\",\n    \"site[0].interfa