{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Please provision an E-Pipe between two routers. Details: Name='Epipe-VLAN-2389-edge-site-to-office', Customer=8362, ServiceID=8298, MTU=1492. Router A (192.168.226.30) port 2/2/c10/1 VLAN 2389, Router B (192.168.105.184) port lag-AMD5-4x10GE VLAN 2389. SDP 30184 for A→B, SDP 18430 for B→A."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2389-edge-site-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8362,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 8298,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.226.30\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c10/1\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2389,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.105.184\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-AMD5-4x10GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2389,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"30184\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.226.30\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.105.184\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"18430\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.105.184\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.226.30\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to deploy an E-Line service. Name: 'Epipe-VLAN-592-campus-to-lab'. Connect customer 3141's sites: Site A at 192.168.222.225 using port lag-Nokia10-2x100GE, Site B at 192.168.33.31 using port lag-Cisco1-2x25GE. VLAN 592, NE service ID 9725, MTU 1400. SDPs: 22531 (forward) and 31225 (reverse)."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-592-campus-to-lab\",\n    \"customer-id\": 3141,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9725,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.222.225\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Nokia10-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 592,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.33.31\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Cisco1-2x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 592,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"22531\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.222.225\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.33.31\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"31225\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.33.31\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.222.225\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our customer (ID: 2963) needs a dedicated Layer 2 connection between their 192.168.228.95 and 192.168.89.67 routers. Please create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-3206-lab-to-edge-site' with service ID 9640. Use VLAN 3206 on ports 1/1/c10/2 (site A) and lag-Arista7-2x25GE (site B). MTU should be 1492. The SDP tunnel IDs are 9567 and 6795."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-3206-lab-to-edge-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 2963,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9640,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.228.95\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c10/2\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3206,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.89.67\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Arista7-2x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3206,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"9567\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.228.95\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.89.67\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"6795\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.89.67\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.228.95\"\n  }\n}"}]}
