{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 8152. The connection goes from router 192.168.106.157 (port 2/1/c8/1) to router 192.168.38.246 (port 1/2/c3/1) on VLAN 625. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-625-pop-to-hub', service ID 2595, MTU 1492. Please use SDP IDs 157246 and 246157 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-625-pop-to-hub\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8152,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 2595,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.106.157\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c8/1\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 625,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.38.246\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c3/1\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 625,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"157246\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.106.157\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.38.246\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"246157\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.38.246\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.106.157\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Deploy an ePIPE service 'Epipe-VLAN-1914-colo-to-office' with the following parameters: customer ID 8109, service ID 1668, MTU 1450. Site A is on device 192.168.240.67 port 2/2/c8/1, Site B is on device 192.168.83.181 port lag-HPE2-4x25GE. VLAN tag is 1914. SDP IDs are 67181 (A to B) and 18167 (B to A)."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1914-colo-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8109,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1668,\n    \"mtu\": 1450,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.240.67\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c8/1\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1914,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.83.181\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-HPE2-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1914,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"67181\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.240.67\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.83.181\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"18167\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.83.181\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.240.67\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create epipe 'Epipe-VLAN-2141-colo-to-remote-site' for customer 7780 connecting 192.168.31.216 (port 2/1/c9/2) to 192.168.198.210 (port 2/1/c3/2) on VLAN 2141. Service ID: 4860, MTU: 1450. SDP IDs: 216210 and 210216."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2141-colo-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 7780,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 4860,\n    \"mtu\": 1450,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.31.216\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c9/2\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2141,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.198.210\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c3/2\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2141,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"216210\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.31.216\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.198.210\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"210216\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.198.210\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.31.216\"\n  }\n}"}]}
