{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the TeleOps project, deploy a VPRN named 'VPRN-2405-TeleOps' for customer 5113. Two sites needed: Site 1 (192.168.105.150): service ID 2405, RD 64598:2405, VRF TeleOps-VRF-Import/TeleOps-VRF-Export, interfaces: Atlas-Cluster-Master on port 2/1/c11/1 with IP 10.33.128.59/24; Atlas-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/2/c7/3 with IP 100.73.233.25/28; Atlas-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-AMD1-2x25GE with IP 100.122.27.105/31. Site 2 (192.168.101.63): service ID 2405, RD 65458:2405, VRF TeleOps-VRF-Import/TeleOps-VRF-Export, interfaces: Epsilon-Cluster-Master on port lag-AFOR7-4x10GE with IP 100.97.91.181/24; Epsilon-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Arista6-4x25GE with IP 10.99.27.48/24; Epsilon-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 1/1/c5/2 with IP 172.26.70.44/24."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-2405-TeleOps\",\n    \"customer-id\": 5113,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-2405-TeleOps\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.105.150\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 2405,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64598:2405\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Atlas-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"2/1/c11/1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.33.128.59\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Atlas-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"2/2/c7/3\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.73.233.25\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[0].interface[2].interface-name\": \"Atlas-Cluster-Worker-2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].sap.port-id\": \"lag-AMD1-2x25GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.122.27.105\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 31,\n    \"site[1].site-name\": \"VPRN-2405-TeleOps\",\n    \"site[1].device-id\": \"192.168.101.63\",\n    \"site[1].ne-service-id\": 2405,\n    \"site[1].route-distinguisher\": \"65458:2405\",\n    \"site[1].vrf-import\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[1].vrf-export\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[1].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Epsilon-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-AFOR7-4x10GE\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.97.91.181\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[1].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Epsilon-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Arista6-4x25GE\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.99.27.48\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[1].interface[2].interface-name\": \"Epsilon-Cluster-Worker-2\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].sap.port-id\": \"1/1/c5/2\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.26.70.44\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our network requires a new tunnel from 192.168.140.152 to 192.168.28.91 for service transport. SDP ID is 15291. Let's call it 'SDP-from-192-168-140-152-to-192-168-28-91'. Use BGP-based MPLS."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.140.152\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"15291\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.28.91\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-140-152-to-192-168-28-91\"\n  }\n}"}]}
