{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "New E-Pipe: 'Epipe-VLAN-2970-hub-to-headquarters' | Cust: 9097 | SvcID: 9779 | MTU: 1492 | A: 192.168.28.214 2/2/c2/2 | B: 192.168.153.145 1/2/c7/2 | VLAN: 2970 | SDP: 214145, 145214"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2970-hub-to-headquarters\",\n    \"customer-id\": 9097,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9779,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.28.214\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c2/2\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2970,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.153.145\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c7/2\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2970,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"214145\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.28.214\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.153.145\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"145214\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.153.145\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.28.214\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Can you create an epipe service? I need to connect 192.168.221.17 to 192.168.52.174. Customer ID is 4832, service name 'Epipe-VLAN-229-remote-site-to-datacenter'. Port 2/1/c10/1 on site A, port 2/2/c10/1 on site B, VLAN 229. NE service ID 7249, MTU 1400, SDPs 17174 and 17417."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-229-remote-site-to-datacenter\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4832,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 7249,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.221.17\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c10/1\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 229,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.52.174\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c10/1\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 229,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"17174\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.221.17\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.52.174\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"17417\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.52.174\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.221.17\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Deploy L3 VPN 'VPRN-1782-FastTrack' for customer 1247. Single site on device 192.168.140.138, NE service ID 1782. RD: 65345:1782. Import policy: FastTrack-VRF-Import, export policy: FastTrack-VRF-Export. Configure the following interfaces: Castor-Cluster-Master on port lag-AFOR8-2x25GE with IP 100.66.156.197/30."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-1782-FastTrack\",\n    \"customer-id\": 1247,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-1782-FastTrack\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.140.138\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 1782,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65345:1782\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"FastTrack-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"FastTrack-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Castor-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-AFOR8-2x25GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.66.156.197\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 30\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need an SDP tunnel between routers 192.168.155.180 and 192.168.206.242. Use BGP signaling with SDP ID 180242. Name it 'SDP-from-192-168-155-180-to-192-168-206-242'."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.155.180\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"180242\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.206.242\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-155-180-to-192-168-206-242\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 4748. The connection goes from router 192.168.255.238 (port 1/2/c1/4) to router 192.168.75.120 (port 2/1/c1/4) on VLAN 2790. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-2790-campus-to-remote-site', service ID 3664, MTU 9192. Please use SDP IDs 238120 and 120238 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2790-campus-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4748,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 3664,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.255.238\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c1/4\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2790,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.75.120\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c1/4\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2790,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"238120\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.255.238\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.75.120\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"120238\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.75.120\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.255.238\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create a VPRN L3 VPN service named 'VPRN-3105-OptiRoute' for customer 4753 with two sites. Site 1 on device 192.168.1.11 (service ID 3105, RD 65342:3105, VRF OptiRoute-VRF-Import/OptiRoute-VRF-Export): Gamma-Cluster-Master on port 1/1/c5/4 with IP 172.20.10.140/24; Gamma-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Juniper4-2x25GE with IP 100.75.12.144/31; Gamma-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 1/1/c6/4 with IP 10.205.103.187/28. Site 2 on device 192.168.195.154 (service ID 3105, RD 65241:3105, VRF OptiRoute-VRF-Import/OptiRoute-VRF-Export): Saturn-Cluster-Master on port lag-Intel1-2x25GE with IP 10.45.29.15/24; Saturn-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/1/c3/2 with IP 172.30.58.187/30; Saturn-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Intel3-4x10GE with IP 172.24.33.86/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-3105-OptiRoute\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4753,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-3105-OptiRoute\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.1.11\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 3105,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65342:3105\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"OptiRoute-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"OptiRoute-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Gamma-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/1/c5/4\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.20.10.140\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Gamma-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Juniper4-2x25GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.75.12.144\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 31,\n    \"site[0].interface[2].interface-name\": \"Gamma-Cluster-Worker-2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].sap.port-id\": \"1/1/c6/4\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.205.103.187\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[1].site-name\": \"VPRN-3105-OptiRoute\",\n    \"site[1].device-id\": \"192.168.195.154\",\n    \"site[1].ne-service-id\": 3105,\n    \"site[1].route-distinguisher\": \"65241:3105\",\n    \"site[1].vrf-import\": [\n      \"OptiRoute-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[1].vrf-export\": [\n      \"OptiRoute-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[1].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Saturn-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Intel1-2x25GE\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.45.29.15\",\n    \"site[1].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[1].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Saturn-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"2/1/c3/2\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.30.58.187\",\n    \"site[1].interface[1].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 30,\n    \"site[1].interface[2].interface-name\": \"Saturn-Cluster-Worker-2\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Intel3-4x10GE\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.24.33.86\",\n    \"site[1].interface[2].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28\n  }\n}"}]}
