{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 9211. The connection goes from router 192.168.255.35 (port 1/1/c4/3) to router 192.168.161.202 (port 1/2/c12/3) on VLAN 1994. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-1994-branch-to-branch', service ID 1781, MTU 1400. Please use SDP IDs 35202 and 20235 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1994-branch-to-branch\",\n    \"customer-id\": 9211,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1781,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.255.35\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c4/3\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1994,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.161.202\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c12/3\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1994,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"35202\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.255.35\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.161.202\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"20235\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.161.202\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.255.35\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Can you create an epipe service? I need to connect 192.168.156.95 to 192.168.206.240. Customer ID is 3320, service name 'Epipe-VLAN-1044-remote-site-to-remote-site'. Port 1/2/c3/3 on site A, port lag-HPE9-2x100GE on site B, VLAN 1044. NE service ID 2269, MTU 9000, SDPs 95240 and 24095."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1044-remote-site-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 3320,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 2269,\n    \"mtu\": 9000,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.156.95\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c3/3\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1044,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.206.240\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-HPE9-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1044,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"95240\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.156.95\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.206.240\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"24095\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.206.240\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.156.95\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Set up an E-Line point-to-point Ethernet service. Service name: 'Epipe-VLAN-1939-office-to-edge-site'. Customer: 5682. NE service ID: 8345. MTU: 1400. Site A: device 192.168.32.69, port 2/1/c8/3, VLAN 1939. Site B: device 192.168.213.228, port 1/2/c10/4, VLAN 1939. Use SDP 69228 from A to B and SDP 22869 from B to A."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1939-office-to-edge-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 5682,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 8345,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.32.69\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c8/3\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1939,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.213.228\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c10/4\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1939,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"69228\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.32.69\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.213.228\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"22869\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.213.228\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.32.69\"\n  }\n}"}]}
