{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a VPRN L3 VPN named 'VPRN-5723-UltraPath' for customer 408 spanning two sites. The first site is on 192.168.167.127 with service ID 5723 and RD 65417:5723. VRF policies: UltraPath-VRF-Import/UltraPath-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Zeta-Cluster-Master on port lag-Intel6-2x100GE with IP 172.24.156.101/31; Zeta-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Cisco6-4x25GE with IP 100.70.194.139/30; Zeta-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Juniper7-2x100GE with IP 100.92.130.85/31. The second site is on 192.168.181.238 with service ID 5723 and RD 65406:5723. VRF policies: UltraPath-VRF-Import/UltraPath-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Deneb-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c11/4 with IP 10.137.101.202/28; Deneb-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Juniper9-4x25GE with IP 100.127.110.112/28; Deneb-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/1/c9/3 with IP 10.15.235.122/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-5723-UltraPath\",\n    \"customer-id\": 408,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-5723-UltraPath\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.167.127\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 5723,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65417:5723\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"UltraPath-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"UltraPath-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].inter