{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the new service deployment, we need an MPLS tunnel between routers 192.168.69.222 and 192.168.35.71. Assign SDP ID 22271 and name it 'SDP-from-192-168-69-222-to-192-168-35-71'. Enable BGP tunnel with TLDP signaling."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.69.222\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"22271\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.35.71\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-69-222-to-192-168-35-71\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Set up an E-Line point-to-point Ethernet service. Service name: 'Epipe-VLAN-3589-datacenter-to-edge-site'. Customer: 3595. NE service ID: 1060. MTU: 9100. Site A: device 192.168.168.42, port lag-Mellanox10-2x25GE, VLAN 3589. Site B: device 192.168.53.117, port 2/2/c4/4, VLAN 3589. Use SDP 42117 from A to B and SDP 11742 from B to A."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-3589-datacenter-to-edge-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 3595,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1060,\n    \"mtu\": 9100,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.168.42\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Mellanox10-2x25GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3589,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.53.117\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c4/4\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3589,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"42117\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.168.42\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.53.117\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"11742\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.53.117\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.168.42\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 7280. The connection goes from router 192.168.164.5 (port 1/2/c7/4) to router 192.168.184.224 (port lag-Dell-NAR12-2x100GE) on VLAN 188. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-188-headquarters-to-hub', service ID 4826, MTU 1450. Please use SDP IDs 5224 and 2245 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-188-headquarters-to-hub\",\n    \"customer-id\": 7280,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 4826,\n    \"mtu\": 1450,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.164.5\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c7/4\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 188,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.184.224\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Dell-NAR12-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 188,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"5224\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.164.5\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.184.224\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"2245\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.184.224\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.164.5\"\n  }\n}"}]}
