{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a point-to-point Ethernet connection between 192.168.143.24 and 192.168.22.236. The service is for customer 6103, called 'Epipe-VLAN-949-remote-site-to-colo'. Site A uses port lag-Broadcom3-2x100GE, site B uses 1/2/c11/2, both on VLAN 949. Service ID is 8511 and MTU should be 1500. SDPs are 24236 and 23624."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-949-remote-site-to-colo\",\n    \"customer-id\": 6103,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 8511,\n    \"mtu\": 1500,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.143.24\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Broadcom3-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 949,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.22.236\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c11/2\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 949,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"24236\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.143.24\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.22.236\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"23624\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.22.236\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.143.24\"\n  }\n}"}]}
