{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to deploy an E-Line service. Name: 'Epipe-VLAN-2429-campus-to-colo'. Connect customer 7933's sites: Site A at 192.168.245.71 using port lag-Dell-NAR6-4x10GE, Site B at 192.168.48.204 using port lag-Broadcom3-2x100GE. VLAN 2429, NE service ID 8105, MTU 9192. SDPs: 71204 (forward) and 20471 (reverse)."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2429-campus-to-colo\",\n    \"customer-id\": 7933,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 8105,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.245.71\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Dell-NAR6-4x10GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2429,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.48.204\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Broadcom3-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2429,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"71204\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.245.71\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.48.204\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"20471\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.48.204\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.245.71\"\n  }\n}"}]}
