{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a VPRN L3 VPN named 'VPRN-2344-HyperNet' for customer 1688 spanning two sites. The first site is on 192.168.11.108 with service ID 2344 and RD 65507:2344. VRF policies: HyperNet-VRF-Import/HyperNet-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Eta-Cluster-Master on port lag-AFOR1-2x25GE with IP 172.28.194.177/28; Eta-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Arista9-2x25GE with IP 172.24.68.205/31; Eta-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/2/c11/4 with IP 172.20.77.176/28. The second site is on 192.168.195.214 with service ID 2344 and RD 65145:2344. VRF policies: HyperNet-VRF-Import/HyperNet-VRF-Export. Interfaces: Nova-Cluster-Master on port 1/1/c1/3 with IP 10.15.99.162/28; Nova-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Broadcom11-2x100GE with IP 10.180.252.34/24; Nova-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/2/c9/3 with IP 172.22.80.38/31."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-2344-HyperNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 1688,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-2344-HyperNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.11.108\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 2344,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65507:2344\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"HyperNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"HyperNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Eta