{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our customer (ID: 6698) needs a dedicated Layer 2 connection between their 192.168.191.99 and 192.168.250.79 routers. Please create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-2626-pop-to-office' with service ID 1636. Use VLAN 2626 on ports 1/1/c7/3 (site A) and lag-Nokia9-2x100GE (site B). MTU should be 1500. The SDP tunnel IDs are 9979 and 7999."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2626-pop-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 6698,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1636,\n    \"mtu\": 1500,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.191.99\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c7/3\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2626,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.250.79\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Nokia9-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2626,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"9979\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.191.99\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.250.79\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"7999\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.250.79\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.191.99\"\n  }\n}"}]}
