{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 6132. The connection goes from router 192.168.154.174 (port lag-Mellanox2-4x25GE) to router 192.168.203.150 (port lag-AMD6-4x25GE) on VLAN 420. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-420-datacenter-to-remote-site', service ID 5631, MTU 9192. Please use SDP IDs 174150 and 150174 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-420-datacenter-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 6132,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 5631,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.154.174\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Mellanox2-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 420,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.203.150\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-AMD6-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 420,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"174150\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.154.174\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.203.150\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"150174\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.203.150\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.154.174\"\n  }\n}"}]}
