{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-3543-remote-site-to-office' for customer 68 (NE service ID 6095). Connect device 192.168.18.118 on port lag-Intel2-4x25GE to device 192.168.198.183 on port 1/1/c9/3 using VLAN 3543. MTU is 1492. Use SDP 118183 and 183118."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-3543-remote-site-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 68,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 6095,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.18.118\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Intel2-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3543,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.198.183\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c9/3\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 3543,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"118183\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.18.118\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.198.183\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"183118\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.198.183\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.18.118\"\n  }\n}"}]}
