{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-2579-hub-to-lab' for customer 2484 (NE service ID 9677). Connect device 192.168.136.96 on port lag-HPE7-2x100GE to device 192.168.212.93 on port lag-Mellanox9-4x25GE using VLAN 2579. MTU is 1400. Use SDP 9693 and 9396."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2579-hub-to-lab\",\n    \"customer-id\": 2484,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9677,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.136.96\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-HPE7-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2579,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.212.93\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Mellanox9-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2579,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"9693\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.136.96\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.212.93\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"9396\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.212.93\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.136.96\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to provision a two-site L3 VPN for customer 4467. Service name: 'VPRN-7133-PrimeNet'. Site A at 192.168.146.167: svc-id 7133, RD 64757:7133, VRF PrimeNet-VRF-Import/PrimeNet-VRF-Export, interfaces: Pluto-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c12/4 with IP 172.26.70.151/30; Pluto-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/2/c1/3 with IP 10.122.243.100/28; Pluto-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/2/c6/2 with IP 10.245.215.120/30. Site B at 192.168.45.20: svc-id 7133, RD 64836:7133, VRF PrimeNet-VRF-Import/PrimeNet-VRF-Export, interfaces: Rigel-Cluster-Master on port lag-AFOR11-4x10GE with IP 10.106.30.160/30; Rigel-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 1/1/c12/3 with IP 172.17.209.96/30; Rigel-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Nokia4-4x25GE with IP 100.95.170.168/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-7133-PrimeNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4467,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-7133-PrimeNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.146.167\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 7133,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64757:7133\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"PrimeNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"PrimeNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Pluto-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port