{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to set up a new E-Pipe service for customer 5986. The connection goes from router 192.168.155.103 (port 2/2/c11/2) to router 192.168.28.162 (port 1/2/c11/2) on VLAN 4084. Name it 'Epipe-VLAN-4084-hub-to-office', service ID 9759, MTU 9212. Please use SDP IDs 103162 and 162103 for the tunnel."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-4084-hub-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 5986,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 9759,\n    \"mtu\": 9212,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.155.103\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c11/2\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 4084,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.28.162\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c11/2\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 4084,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"103162\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.155.103\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.28.162\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"162103\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.28.162\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.155.103\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the CloudX project, deploy a VPRN named 'VPRN-3141-CloudX' for customer 758. Two sites needed: Site 1 (192.168.61.218): service ID 3141, RD 65087:3141, VRF CloudX-VRF-Import/CloudX-VRF-Export, interfaces: Kappa-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c1/3 with IP 172.27.64.61/28; Kappa-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Nokia9-4x25GE with IP 100.107.82.152/30. Site 2 (192.168.63.20): service ID 3141, RD 64951:3141, VRF CloudX-VRF-Import/CloudX-VRF-Export, interfaces: Jupiter-Cluster-Master on port lag-AFOR8-4x25GE with IP 172.30.42.73/31; Jupiter-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/1/c10/4 with IP 100.78.158.235/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-3141-CloudX\",\n    \"customer-id\": 758,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-3141-CloudX\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.61.218\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 3141,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65087:3141\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"CloudX-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"CloudX-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Kappa-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/2/c1/3\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.27.64.61\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-le