{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our customer (ID: 472) needs a dedicated Layer 2 connection between their 192.168.144.187 and 192.168.96.108 routers. Please create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-739-colo-to-campus' with service ID 5754. Use VLAN 739 on ports 2/1/c6/4 (site A) and 2/1/c6/4 (site B). MTU should be 9192. The SDP tunnel IDs are 187108 and 108187."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-739-colo-to-campus\",\n    \"customer-id\": 472,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 5754,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.144.187\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c6/4\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 739,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.96.108\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c6/4\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 739,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"187108\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.144.187\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.96.108\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"108187\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.96.108\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.144.187\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the network upgrade project, provision an epipe service 'Epipe-VLAN-564-remote-site-to-headquarters'. Customer 6522 requires a point-to-point connection. Source router: 192.168.190.114, port: 1/1/c12/2. Destination router: 192.168.39.147, port: 2/1/c5/3. Common VLAN: 564. Service ID: 6150. MTU: 9192. Use existing SDPs 114147 and 147114."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-564-remote-site-to-headquarters\",\n    \"customer-id\": 6522,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 6150,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.190.114\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c12/2\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 564,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.39.147\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c5/3\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 564,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"114147\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.190.114\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.39.147\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"147114\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.39.147\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.190.114\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to deploy an E-Line service. Name: 'Epipe-VLAN-1941-datacenter-to-remote-site'. Connect customer 7272's sites: Site A at 192.168.49.64 using port lag-Juniper7-2x100GE, Site B at 192.168.104.27 using port lag-Cisco9-4x25GE. VLAN 1941, NE service ID 7401, MTU 1492. SDPs: 6427 (forward) and 2764 (reverse)."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1941-datacenter-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 7272,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 7401,\n    \"mtu\": 1492,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.49.64\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Juniper7-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1941,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.104.27\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Cisco9-4x25GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1941,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"6427\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.49.64\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.104.27\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"2764\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.104.27\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.49.64\"\n  }\n}"}]}
