{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the StarNet project, create a VPRN L3 VPN named 'VPRN-6582-StarNet'. Customer 1963 requires connectivity on device 192.168.16.202 with service ID 6582. Route distinguisher: 65367:6582. Import policy: StarNet-VRF-Import, export: StarNet-VRF-Export. Interfaces needed: Atlas-Cluster-Master on port 1/1/c5/2 with IP 10.159.217.76/30; Atlas-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Dell-NAR9-4x25GE with IP 100.83.143.88/24; Atlas-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/2/c3/1 with IP 100.103.153.105/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-6582-StarNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 1963,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-6582-StarNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.16.202\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 6582,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65367:6582\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"StarNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"StarNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Atlas-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/1/c5/2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.159.217.76\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 30,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Atlas-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1]