{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our customer (ID: 1201) needs a dedicated Layer 2 connection between their 192.168.78.7 and 192.168.235.184 routers. Please create an E-Pipe service named 'Epipe-VLAN-1359-datacenter-to-office' with service ID 1889. Use VLAN 1359 on ports lag-Broadcom2-2x25GE (site A) and lag-Arista7-2x100GE (site B). MTU should be 9000. The SDP tunnel IDs are 7184 and 1847."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-1359-datacenter-to-office\",\n    \"customer-id\": 1201,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1889,\n    \"mtu\": 9000,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.78.7\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Broadcom2-2x25GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1359,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.235.184\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Arista7-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 1359,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"7184\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.78.7\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.235.184\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"1847\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.235.184\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.78.7\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the TeleOps project, create a VPRN L3 VPN named 'VPRN-1894-TeleOps'. Customer 449 requires connectivity on device 192.168.72.230 with service ID 1894. Route distinguisher: 65266:1894. Import policy: TeleOps-VRF-Import, export: TeleOps-VRF-Export. Interfaces needed: Phoenix-Cluster-Master on port lag-Mellanox6-2x100GE with IP 10.69.58.53/30; Phoenix-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-AMD11-2x100GE with IP 172.28.97.85/24; Phoenix-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Cisco2-4x25GE with IP 172.29.40.237/30."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-1894-TeleOps\",\n    \"customer-id\": 449,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-1894-TeleOps\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.72.230\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 1894,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65266:1894\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Phoenix-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Mellanox6-2x100GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.69.58.53\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 30,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Phoenix-Cluster-Worker