{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Set up an E-Line point-to-point Ethernet service. Service name: 'Epipe-VLAN-2304-branch-to-datacenter'. Customer: 1387. NE service ID: 3043. MTU: 9192. Site A: device 192.168.105.168, port 1/2/c11/1, VLAN 2304. Site B: device 192.168.82.23, port 1/2/c11/4, VLAN 2304. Use SDP 16823 from A to B and SDP 23168 from B to A."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2304-branch-to-datacenter\",\n    \"customer-id\": 1387,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 3043,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.105.168\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c11/1\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2304,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.82.23\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/2/c11/4\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2304,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"16823\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.105.168\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.82.23\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"23168\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.82.23\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.105.168\"\n  }\n}"}]}
