{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Can you create an epipe service? I need to connect 192.168.13.218 to 192.168.154.53. Customer ID is 3091, service name 'Epipe-VLAN-2121-pop-to-remote-site'. Port lag-Cisco8-2x100GE on site A, port 2/1/c9/1 on site B, VLAN 2121. NE service ID 7418, MTU 9192, SDPs 21853 and 53218."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2121-pop-to-remote-site\",\n    \"customer-id\": 3091,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 7418,\n    \"mtu\": 9192,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.13.218\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-Cisco8-2x100GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2121,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.154.53\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/1/c9/1\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2121,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"21853\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.13.218\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.154.53\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"53218\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.154.53\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.13.218\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our network requires a new tunnel from 192.168.213.156 to 192.168.115.199 for service transport. SDP ID is 156199. Let's call it 'SDP-from-192-168-213-156-to-192-168-115-199'. Use BGP-based MPLS."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.213.156\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"156199\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.115.199\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-213-156-to-192-168-115-199\"\n  }\n}"}]}
