{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create epipe 'Epipe-VLAN-2779-headquarters-to-colo' for customer 9783 connecting 192.168.6.197 (port 2/2/c2/4) to 192.168.121.14 (port 1/1/c4/3) on VLAN 2779. Service ID: 1131, MTU: 1400. SDP IDs: 19714 and 14197."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-2779-headquarters-to-colo\",\n    \"customer-id\": 9783,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 1131,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.6.197\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"2/2/c2/4\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2779,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.121.14\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c4/3\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 2779,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"19714\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.6.197\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.121.14\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"14197\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.121.14\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.6.197\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "For the new service deployment, we need an MPLS tunnel between routers 192.168.44.72 and 192.168.230.63. Assign SDP ID 7263 and name it 'SDP-from-192-168-44-72-to-192-168-230-63'. Enable BGP tunnel with TLDP signaling."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.44.72\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"7263\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.230.63\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-44-72-to-192-168-230-63\"\n  }\n}"}]}
