{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create a VPRN L3 VPN service named 'VPRN-8042-FastTrack' for customer 523 with two sites. Site 1 on device 192.168.6.221 (service ID 8042, RD 65492:8042, VRF FastTrack-VRF-Import/FastTrack-VRF-Export): Gamma-Cluster-Master on port lag-Dell-NAR2-4x10GE with IP 100.123.14.219/28; Gamma-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/2/c2/1 with IP 100.110.215.20/24. Site 2 on device 192.168.162.129 (service ID 8042, RD 64732:8042, VRF FastTrack-VRF-Import/FastTrack-VRF-Export): Vega-Cluster-Master on port 2/2/c8/4 with IP 100.115.218.20/24; Vega-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/2/c7/4 with IP 172.29.249.172/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-8042-FastTrack\",\n    \"customer-id\": 523,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-8042-FastTrack\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.6.221\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 8042,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65492:8042\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"FastTrack-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"FastTrack-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Gamma-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Dell-NAR2-4x10GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.123.14.219\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.pr