{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a Layer 3 VPN for customer 9328. Name it 'VPRN-3727-TeleOps'. There's one site on device 192.168.241.176 with service ID 3727. Use RD 64605:3727, import policy TeleOps-VRF-Import and export policy TeleOps-VRF-Export. The interfaces are: Titan-Cluster-Master on port lag-Mellanox6-2x25GE with IP 10.199.98.218/28; Titan-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 1/1/c10/4 with IP 100.89.165.34/31; Titan-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/1/c10/3 with IP 10.227.123.204/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-3727-TeleOps\",\n    \"customer-id\": 9328,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-3727-TeleOps\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.241.176\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 3727,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64605:3727\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"TeleOps-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Titan-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Mellanox6-2x25GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.199.98.218\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Titan-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"1/1/c10/4\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.89.165.34\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 31,\n    \"site[0].interface[2].interface-name\": \"Titan-Cluster-Worker-2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].sap.port-id\": \"2/1/c10/3\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.227.123.204\",\n    \"site[0].interface[2].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Deploy L3 VPN 'VPRN-2825-CloudX' for customer 2293. Single site on device 192.168.99.40, NE service ID 2825. RD: 65469:2825. Import policy: CloudX-VRF-Import, export policy: CloudX-VRF-Export. Configure the following interfaces: Vega-Cluster-Master on port 2/1/c4/3 with IP 100.126.43.116/28; Vega-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Broadcom9-2x100GE with IP 100.85.15.50/28."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-2825-CloudX\",\n    \"customer-id\": 2293,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-2825-CloudX\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.99.40\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 2825,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65469:2825\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"CloudX-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"CloudX-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Vega-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"2/1/c4/3\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.126.43.116\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Vega-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Broadcom9-2x100GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"100.85.15.50\",\n   